{"recipe_desc": "Pixar commissioned commissioned the famous chef Thomas Keller to create an amazing ratatouille recipe for them to 'use' in their film Ratatouille. This recipe is what Remy makes at the end of the film. To make it easier to get the vegetables sliced thinly, I recommend using a <a href='http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0000632QE/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B0000632QE&linkCode=as2&tag=makbetfoo-20'>mandoline</a><img src='http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=makbetfoo-20&l=as2&o=1&a=B0000632QE' width='1' height='1' border='0' alt='' style='border:none !important; margin:0px !important;' />. If you want to get fancy with the spices, this recipe can also be called Confit Byaldi. As for me, I just call it delicious.", "recipe_category": ["Entrees"], "recipe_image": ["/recipes/ratatouille-a-la-remy/ratatouille-a-la-remy.jpg"], "recipe_total_time": ["PT3H45M"], "recipe_published_time": ["Sep 17, 2012"], "image_urls": ["http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/ratatouille-a-la-remy/ratatouille-a-la-remy.jpg"], "recipe_ingredients": ["1 yellow pepper", "1 orange pepper", "2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil", "2 cloves garlic, minced", "\u00bd small yellow onion, finely diced", "3 tomatoes (12 ounces total)", "1 bay leaf", "reserved peppers", "\u00bd teaspoon salt, or to taste", "1 medium zucchini", "1 medium yellow squash", "1 Japanese eggplant", "4 Roma tomatoes", "2 teaspoons olive oil", "\u00bd teaspoon minced garlic", "\u00bc teaspoon salt", "1/8 teaspoon thyme", "1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper", "reserved piperade", "1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil", "1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar", "\u00bc teaspoon thyme", "\u00bc teaspoon salt", "1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper."], "recipe_prep_time": ["PT45M"], "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<title>Ratatouille a la Remy Recipe - MakeBetterFood.com</title>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html;charse