rown.", "Season with salt and remove bay leaf.", "Reserve one tablespoon of the sauce and spread the remainder in bottom of a round casserole dish.", "Reduce oven temperature to 275\u00b0F.", "Using a mandoline or sharp knife, slice vegetables into 1/16-inch rounds, reserving each vegetable in a small bowl.", "Down center of pan, arrange a strip of 8 alternating slices of vegetables over piperade, overlapping so that \u00bc inch of each slice is exposed. Around the center strip, overlap vegetables in a close spiral that lets slices mound slightly toward center. Repeat until pan is filled; not all vegetables may be needed.", "Mix garlic, oil, salt, thyme, and pepper in a small bowl. Drizzle evenly over vegetables.", "Cover pan with foil and crimp edges to seal well.", "Bake until vegetables are tender when tested with a paring knife, about 2 hours. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more. Lightly cover with foil if it starts to brown.", "If there is excess liquid in pan, place over medium heat on stove until reduced. At this point it may be cooled, covered and refrigerated for up to 2 days. Serve cold or reheat in 350-degree oven until warm.", "Combine reserved piperade, oil, vinegar, thyme, salt, and pepper in a bowl.", "To serve, very carefully lift desired portion onto plate with an offset spatula and either align vegetables in a row or gently turn to fan them out onto plate. Drizzle vinaigrette around plate. Serve hot."], "images": [{"url": "http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/ratatouille-a-la-remy/ratatouille-a-la-remy.jpg", "path": "full/1c62611f92f9af906df203110d3d317bfe70ef6f.jpg", "checksum": "b942bae0a632d4fd545975e2cbd0fcc7"}], "link": "http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/ratatouille-a-la-remy/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT3H"], "recipe_yield": ["Serves 4 to 6"]}